<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10774] Fail stream session if receiver cannot process data</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10774</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tjake&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tjake&quot;&gt;tjake&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10674&quot; title=&quot;Materialized View SSTable streaming/leaving status race on decommission&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10674&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10674&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think the underlying issue here is streaming failures only account for problems during the file send. Not any subsequent errors.&lt;br/&gt;
We should probably add an acknowledgement to the streaming operation that it was processed by the receiver correctly.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems the stream receive task (and thus the stream sesssion) is only completed on &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-2.1/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/streaming/StreamReceiveTask.java#L175&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.1&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-2.2/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/streaming/StreamReceiveTask.java#L171&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.2&lt;/a&gt; after the files are processed (otherwise it just hangs), but on &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-3.0/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/streaming/StreamReceiveTask.java#L231&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.0&lt;/a&gt; it&apos;s always completed even if there was a failure, what seems more critical. In any case, we should probably fail the stream session if there is a problem while processing the received data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
