                            <comment id="15030340" author="pauloricardomg" created="Sat, 28 Nov 2015 01:47:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was able to confirm the suspicion by injecting an exception on the &lt;tt&gt;OnCompletionRunnable&lt;/tt&gt; of the receiving node during a ccm testing bootstrap session. On 2.1 and 2.2, the bootstrap hangs indefinitely, while on 3.0 the bootstrap succeeds even with a failure during processing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simple fix is to wrap the &lt;tt&gt;OnCompletionRunnable.run()&lt;/tt&gt; in a try-catch block, and fail the stream session in case an exception is catch. Otherwise the stream receive task is completed as usual. I tested with a similar scenario as before and the bootstrap fails as expected in 2.1, 2.2 and 3.0.&lt;/p&gt;

